Sola Shittu Benin Unknown gunmen on Friday abducted a Catholic Priest serving at the Uromi Diocese of Edo State, Rev Father Nicholas Oboh, in Benin City. Chancellor of the diocese, Rev Father Osi Odenore, who confirmed this in a statement posted on his Facebook page, said Rev Father Oboh was abducted on Valentine’s day, but was not specific on the area where the abduction took place. “We call for prayers for the release of Father Oboh. “We are sure he is alive, and since the incident, steps have been taken to ensure that Rev Father Nicholas Oboh is released without harm,” he said. Similarly four children were reportedly abducted at Umelu community in Ikpoba-Okha Local Government Area. It was gathered that armed robbers had robbed residents in the area and took four children along with them. Sources in the area said one of the abducted children has been released after the parents paid the sum of N2m. The sources said other parents have opened negotiations with the abductors. The Edo State Police spokesman, DSP Chidi Nwabuzor, however, said he had not been briefed on the incidents Copyright PUNCH.
